  <h2>Parents and ESEA</h2>

<!--BEGIN CONTENT-->

<p>Parental involvement is a critical component of the Elementary and Secondary  Education Act (ESEA), which used to be called the No Child Left Behind Act  (NCLB), a federal law affecting K-12 education. ESEA provides funding for extra  help for students, and holds schools accountable for outcomes. Please visit the  links below for more information. </p>
<ul type="disc">
  <li><a href="http://education.state.mn.us/MDE/SchSup/ESEA/index.html" target="_blank">Minnesota       Department of Education &ndash; Federal Title Programs</a>  </li>
  <li><a href="http://education.state.mn.us/MDE/SchSup/ESEA/WorkParent/index.html" target="_blank">Minnesota       Department of Education &ndash; Working with Parents</a></li>
  <li><a href="http://www2.ed.gov/nclb/landing.jhtml" target="_blank">US       Department of Education &ndash; ESEA/NCLB</a></li>
</ul>
<h3>How are Minnesota schools performing? </h3>
<ul type="disc">
  <li><a href="http://mpls.startribune.com/dynamic/no_child/district.php" target="_blank">Test       Results for Minnesota Schools</a></li>
  <li><a href="http://education.state.mn.us/MDE/JustParent/AYP/index.html" target="_blank">More About       AYP</a>  </li>
</ul>
<p>NCLB says that all public schools have to meet some basic standards. If your  child&rsquo;s school is not meeting those standards after two years, your child may  be able to receive two services, supplemental educational services (SES) and  school choice. </p>
<ul type="disc">
  <li><a href="http://education.state.mn.us/MDE/StuSuc/Tutor/index.html" target="_blank">SES in       Minnesota</a>  </li>
  <li><a href="http://education.state.mn.us/MDE/JustParent/SchChoice/index.html" target="_blank">School       Choice in Minnesota</a>&nbsp;  </li>
</ul>
<p>NCLB also says that public school teachers need to be highly qualified. </p>
<ul type="disc">
  <li><a href="http://education.state.mn.us/MDE/EdExc/Licen/index.html" target="_blank">Learn more       about Minnesota teacher standards</a>  </li>
  <li><a href="http://education.state.mn.us/MDE/EdExc/Licen/TeachLicLook/index.html" target="_blank">Learn more       about a teacher's license</a>  </li>
</ul>
